    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Keeping Late Hours</strong>&mdash;The habit of sitting up late at night is customary; but it is not pleasing to God, even if you are both Christians. These untimely hours injure health, unfit the mind for the next day&apos;s duties, and have an appearance of evil. My brother, I hope you will have self-respect enough to shun this form of courtship. If you have an eye single to the glory of God, you will move with deliberate caution. You will not suffer lovesick sentimentalism to so blind your vision that you cannot discern the high claims that God has upon you as a Christian.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">3<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"3T 44.1\" data-link=\"119.195\">Testimonies for the Church 3:44, 45</span>.</span></a></sup>",
