    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "This disposition will reveal itself in the married life. The marriage relation does not always make the fickle mind firm, the wavering steadfast and true to principle. They tire of constancy, and unholy thoughts will manifest themselves in unholy actions. How essential it is, then, that the youth so gird up the loins of their mind and guard their conduct that Satan cannot beguile them from the path of uprightness.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 11-4-1884\" data-link=\"821.5939\">The Review and Herald, November 4, 1884</span>.</span></a></sup>",
