    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Those who would preserve physical health, a vigorous intellect, and sound morals must &ldquo;flee ... youthful lusts.&rdquo; Those who will put forth zealous and decided efforts to check the wickedness that lifts its bold, presumptuous head in our midst are hated and maligned by all wrongdoers, but they will be honored and recompensed of God.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">8<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"ST 7-1-1903\" data-link=\"820.18673\">The Signs of the Times, July 1, 1903</span>.</span></a></sup>",
